fields.label: Project Management
fields.description: The discipline of project management, the activities which comprise this area and the variables implied in it, such as time, resources, requirements, deadlines, and responding to unexpected events.

fields.label: First Aid
fields.description: The emergency treatment given to a sick or injured person in the case of circulatory and/or respiratory failure, unconsciousness, wounds, bleeding, shock or poisoning.

fields.label: Team Leadership
fields.description: Lead, supervise and motivate a group of people, in order to meet the expected results within a given timeline and with the foreseen resources in mind.

fields.label: Order supplies
fields.description: Command products from relevant suppliers to get convenient and profitable products to purchase.

fields.name: Riverbank Restoration Day
fields.description: Volunteers work along the local riverbank to remove litter, trim invasive plants, and stabilize the soil with native vegetation. First aid may be required for cuts, insect bites, or slips on muddy terrain.

fields.name: Relief Route Rally
fields.description: Volunteers coordinate logistics and transport of essential supplies to affected communities after a storm or flood.

fields.name: First Aid Force
fields.description: Certified and trained volunteers provide immediate medical aid and triage support at disaster relief sites and evacuation centers.

fields.name: Beach Clean-Up
fields.description: Volunteers gather along the coast or riverside, carrying bags and moving uneven surfacesùhazards include slips, cuts, sun/heat exposure.

fields.name: Big Tree Planting Initiative
fields.description: A large-scale tree-planting by volunteers, often on rough ground, using toolsùrisks include tool-related accidents, muscle strain, heat exhaustion.

fields.name: Event First Aid Support Crew
fields.description: Volunteers trained in first aid provide on-site assistance at large community events (e.g. races, fairs, or concerts). Tasks include monitoring hydration stations, handling minor injuries, and alerting emergency responders.
